
1. required dependencies (including their development packages:
    zlib
    tiff
    jpeg
    png
    fftw3
    fftw3f
    hdf5
    openexr
    valgrind
    python3 numpy, nosetests, sphinx
    boost-python3
    boost-graph
    boost-threads
    boost-timer
    
NOTE: These are installed system-wide (i.e. not just in scipyen virtual environment)
TODO: Contemplate installing these inside the virtual environment
    
The following steps must be made with with scipyen-virtualenv activated, i.e., 
the X terminal prompt should look something like: 
    " (scipyen-virtualenv) user@host~> "

# saye your git repo clones are in ~/git_repositories

(scipyen-virtualenv) user@host~> cd git_repositories
(scipyen-virtualenv) user@host~/git_repositories>
(scipyen-virtualenv) user@host~/git_repositories> git clone https://github.com/ukoethe/vigra.git
(scipyen-virtualenv) user@host~/git_repositories> mkdir vigra-build
(scipyen-virtualenv) user@host~/git_repositories> cd vigra-build
(scipyen-virtualenv) user@host~/git_repositories/vigra-build> cmake-gui

# Options inside cmake-gui (or if using cmake cli) -- NOTE: replace "user" with your account name
    CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX (-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=) /home/user/scipyen-virtualenv
    LIB_SUFFIX (-DLIB_SUFFIX=) 64


After pressing "Configure" button in cmake-gui, in the output console of
cmake-gui you should get something like this:
    
---------------------------------------------------------
  building shared lib
  binaries will be generated in: /home/cezar/git_repositories/vigra-build
  manuals will be generated in: /home/cezar/git_repositories/vigra/doc
---------------------------------------------------------
  includes will be installed at: /home/cezar/scipyen-virtualenv/include
  libraries will be installed at: /home/cezar/scipyen-virtualenv/lib64
  binaries will be installed at: /home/cezar/scipyen-virtualenv/bin
  vigra manuals will be installed at: /home/cezar/scipyen-virtualenv/doc/vigra/index.html
  vigranumpy will be installed at /home/cezar/scipyen-virtualenv/lib64/python3.6/site-packages
  vigranumpy manuals will be installed at: /home/cezar/scipyen-virtualenv/doc/vigranumpy/html/index.html
---------------------------------------------------------
Configuring done    

Press "Generate" to create a makefile

Close cmake-gui; then, back in console, execute "make" then "make install" to
install vigra inside the virtual environment tree

NOTE: during all this time the console operates in the context of the "active"
scipyen virtual environment

